   "source": [
    "# Exploratory Data Analysis: Analyzing California Wildfires from 2000-2023\n",
    "#### Data Source: California Open Data Portal\n",
    "\n",
    "###### The purpose of this notebook is to explore methods of exploratory data analysis utilizing popular data analysis libraries such as pandas, matplotlib, and seaborn. The main questions we'd like to explore in this dataset are:\n",
    "- What have been the general trend for California wildfires over the last 23 years? Overall, do wildfires in California seem to be getting better or worse over time?\n",
    "- What kind of extreme outlier events have occured in the past 23 years?\n",
    "- What are the main causes of wildfires? Have these changed over time?"
   ]
  },
